<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910327-0040</DOCNO><DOCID>910327-0040.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Rochester Gas andamp; Electric Corp.:   Costs Related to Ice Storm   To Cut 1st-Period Earnings</HL><DATE>03/27/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   RGS</CO><IN>ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)</IN><LP>   Rochester Gas andamp; Electric Corp. said costs associated witha recent ice storm will reduce first-quarter earnings by asmuch as seven cents a share.   In addition, the company said the warmer weather will havean &quot;adverse effect&quot; on first-quarter earnings.</LP><TEXT>   In the year-earlier period, net income was $71.4 million,or $2.10 a share, on revenue of $240.8 million.   In a Securities and Exchange Commission filing, theRochester, N.Y., utility estimated the cost of the storm tobe at least $25 million. More than 200,000 RGandamp;E customerslost electric power during the March 3 storm. It took nearlytwo weeks to restore power to some customers because ofmassive system damage in neighborhoods and backyards.</TEXT></DOC>